'''Adam and Steve''' is a phrase that originated from the [[Judeo-Christian]] argument against [[homosexuality]], in which [[theologian]]s point out that the natural way of life illustrated by the [[Biblical]] account of creation is the story of "[[Adam and Eve]]," a man and a women, as opposed to a a man and a man as in "Adam and Steve."

A movie and a gay dating service have both been named after this term.

